 +4
Common C# Escape Sequences
\n: New line
\t: Horizontal tab
\\: Backslash
\": Double quote
\': Single quote
\r: Carriage return
\a: Alert (bell)
\0: Null character 

Usage Examples
Escaping Quotes: string s = "She said, \"Hello!\"";
File Paths (Normal): string path = "C:\\Files\\data.txt";
File Paths (Verbatim): string path = @"C:\Files\data.txt";
